
	<sn><md>## Course Contents

| Unit / Topic                                                 | Sub-Topics / Details                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| ------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Introduction to Plant Diversity**                          | - Plants of the past and present<br>- Overview of the Plant Kingdom<br>- Classification systems of Plant Kingdom<br>- Major plant groups: algae, bryophytes, pteridophytes, gymnosperms, angiosperms, and their evolutionary relationships                                                                                      |
| **Classification and Characteristics of Major Plant Groups** | - Morphological, anatomical, and reproductive features of:<br>• Prokaryotes<br>• Algae<br>• Fungi and Lichens<br>- Ecological roles with typical examples                                                                                                                                                                       |
