| **Plant Hormones and Growth Regulation**                     | - Functions of plant hormones: auxins, gibberellins, cytokinins, etc.<br>- Growth regulation and response to soil conditions<br>- Physiology of flowering:<br>• Photoperiodism: role of phytochrome, light and dark periods<br>• Vernalization: role of low temperature with reference to winter wheat                          |
