<sn><md>## Course Description{.text-center}

* **Course Code:** 05110201201
* **Course Title:** Diversities in Plant Kingdom and Plant Physiology
* **Course Status:** GED
* **Credit:** 30
* **Year:** Second
</md></sn><sn><md>## Course Learning Outcomes

Upon completion of this course, the students will be able to:

* **CLO1:** Identify and classify major plant groups based on morphological and reproductive characteristics with emphasis on their ecological roles and relevance to soil–plant systems.
* **CLO2:** Describe key physiological processes in plants, including photosynthesis, respiration, water and nutrient uptake, and their influence on plant growth and soil interactions.
* **CLO3:** Apply plant physiology to propose agricultural and land use practices that enhance soil productivity and ecosystem resilience.

